column5:
Fix migration compatibility with Python 2.6

@mbertheau provided a fix in #1176. That commit has been applied to
master. This is fixing the same issue for Oscar 0.6

Don't hide base class get_queryset.

And get the model object name from the model attribute that
get_object_dict expects to exist anyway. Reason:

class OscarListView(generic.ListView):
    def get_queryset(self):
        ...

class CustomListView(BulkEditMixin, OscarListView):
    # calling get_queryset on this class would resolve to BulkEditMixin.
    # get_queryset and return None.

Remove MultiFacetedSearch{View,Form}

These classes have been removed in favour of the new search structure
developed for Oscar's demo site.

Adjust bankcard model to provide an obfuscated number property

Useful in templates where the bankcard form is rendered.  Eg:

    {{ bankcard_form.bankcard.obfuscated_number }}

Moved responsive JS into own object

Not 100% sure what this section does.  Could do with some advice from
@informa.

Split field rendering into a separate template

This makes it easier to use the Oscar form mark-up but rending a form
manually.

For example::

	<form action="." method="post">

	    <legend>First set of fields</legend>
		{% include 'partials/form_field.html' with field=form.name %}
		{% include 'partials/form_field.html' with field=form.description %}

	    <legend>Second set of fields</legend>
		{% include 'partials/form_field.html' with field=form.start_date %}
		{% include 'partials/form_field.html' with field=form.end_date %}

	</form>
